{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Matrix profile\n",
    "\n",
    "The matrix profile is a data structure that annotates a time series with the distance\n",
    "of the closest matching subsequence at the i:th index. In these examples, we explore the use of the matrix profile and motif and regime change detection as implemented in terms of it.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Similarity AB-join\n",
    "In the first example, we join\n",
    "every subsequence in the second sample with the first three samples."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.distance import matrix_profile, subsequence_match"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load a dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"GunPoint\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Second, we compute the matrix profile similarity join between the first three samples and the second sample."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mp = matrix_profile(x[0:3], x[1], window=5, exclude=0.2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we plot the samples and the matrix profile"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=3, sharex=True)\n",
    "ax[0].plot(x[1])\n",
    "for i in range(mp.shape[0]):\n",
    "    ax[1].plot(x[i], label=str(i))\n",
    "    ax[2].plot(mp[i], label=str(i))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"A\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"B\")\n",
    "ax[2].set_title(\"Matrix profile\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlim(0, x.shape[-1])\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlim(0, x.shape[-1])\n",
    "ax[2].set_xlim(0, x.shape[-1])\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Similarity self-join\n",
    "\n",
    "In the second example, we self-join every subsequence with its closest position. First, we load a dataset and concatenate the first 20 samples."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"TwoLeadECG\")\n",
    "x = x[:20].reshape(-1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Second, we compute the matrix profile self-join."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mp = matrix_profile(x.reshape(-1), window=20, exclude=0.2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we plot the time series and matrix profile"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=2, sharex=True)\n",
    "ax[0].plot(x, color=\"red\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax[1].plot(mp, color=\"blue\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"Time series\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"Matrix profile\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlim(0, x.shape[-1])\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlim(0, x.shape[-1])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Matrix profile and subsequence distance\n",
    "\n",
    "In the third example, we "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load a dataset concatenating the first 10 samples and extracting a subsequence of 20 timesteps, starting at index 45. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"TwoLeadECG\", preprocess=\"normalize\")\n",
    "x = x[0:10].reshape(-1)\n",
    "subseq = x[45:65]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Second, we compute the distance to all matching same-length subsequences."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "idx, dist = subsequence_match(\n",
    "    subseq.reshape(1, -1), \n",
    "    x.reshape(1, -1), \n",
    "    return_distance=True, \n",
    "    threshold=np.inf, \n",
    "    metric=\"scaled_euclidean\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "do = np.argsort(dist)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we compute the self-join matrix profile."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mp, mpi = matrix_profile(x, window=20, return_index=True)\n",
    "lu = np.argmin(mp)\n",
    "mu = np.argmax(mp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7faf80dcdf10>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(nrows=3, figsize=(12, 6), sharex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"Time series\")\n",
    "ax1.plot(x, color=\"blue\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax1.set_xlim(0, x.size)\n",
    "ax1.axvspan(45, 65, 0, 1, color=\"gray\", alpha=0.2)\n",
    "ax1.annotate(text=\"\", xy=(65, x[65]), xytext=(mpi[45], x[mpi[45]]), arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='<-', lw=0.5))\n",
    "ax1.axvspan(mpi[45], mpi[45]+20, 0, 1, color=\"red\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Best match\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2.set_title(\"Subsequence distance profile\")\n",
    "ax2.plot(idx, dist, color=\"red\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax2.axvspan(45, 65, 0, 1, color=\"gray\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Subsequence\")\n",
    "ax2.annotate(text=\"%.2f\" % dist[do[1]], xy=(do[1], x[do[1]]))\n",
    "ax2.axvline(do[1], 0, 1, color=\"black\", lw=0.5, ls=\"--\", label=\"Best non self-match\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax3.set_title(\"Matrix profile\")\n",
    "ax3.plot(mp, color=\"green\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax3.axvline(lu, 0, 1, color=\"gray\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax3.annotate(text=\"Least unique\", xy=(lu, mp[lu]), xytext=(lu + 10, 4), arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=0.5))\n",
    "ax3.axvline(mu, 0, 1, color=\"gray\", lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax3.annotate(text=\"Most unique\", xy=(mu, mp[mu]), xytext=(mu + 10, 4), arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', lw=0.5))\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()\n",
    "fig.legend(ncol=4, fontsize=8)"
   ]
  }
 ],
